did.unittitle: Jean Marburg League of Women Voters collection
did.abstract: Materials relate to the daily operations and special projects of the League of Women Voters of the Fairfax Area (LWVFA), particularly 1979-1984 when Jean Marburg served on the Executive Board. Materials are representative of LWVFA's focus on many community, social, environmental, and political issues such as nuclear energy, hunger, defense, international development, and trade. Types of materials include reports, correspondence, printed materials, and notes.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Jean Marburg League of Women Voters collection, Collection #C0039, Special Collections and Archives, George Mason University.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Collection donated by Jean Marburg in 1995.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Processed by Special Collections and Archives Staff. EAD markup completed in March 2009 by Eron Ackerman and Jordan Patty.

bioghist.head: Biographical Information
bioghist.p: Jean Marburg served as a member of the Executive Board of the League of Women Voters of the Fairfax Area from 1979-1984.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials relate to the daily operations and special projects of the League of Women Voters of the Fairfax Area (LWVFA), particularly 1979-1984 when Jean Marburg served on the Executive Board. Materials are representative of LWVFA's focus on many community, social, environmental, and political issues such as nuclear energy, hunger, defense, international development and trade. Types of materials include reports, correspondence, printed materials, and notes.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged by subject.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: Special Collections and Archives also holds the League of Women Voters of the Fairfax Area records.
